7 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
8 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 47 O.S. 2021, Section 1135.3, as
9 last amended by Section 1, Chapter 325, O.S.L. 2025 (47 O.S. Supp.
10 2025, Section 1135.3), is amended to read as follows:
11 Section 1135.3. A. Service Oklahoma is hereby authorized to
12 design and issue appropriate official special license plates to
13 persons wishing to demonstrate support, interest or membership to or
14 for an organization, occupation, cause or other subject as provided
15 by this section.
16 Special license plates shall not be transferred to any other
17 person but shall be removed from the vehicle upon transfer of
18 ownership and retained. The special license plate may then be used
19 on another vehicle but only after such other vehicle has been
20 registered for the current year.
21 Special license plates shall be renewed each year by Service
22 Oklahoma or a licensed operator, unless authorized by Service
23 Oklahoma to be renewed for a period greater than one (1) year.
24 Service Oklahoma shall notify by mail all persons issued special
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - HB4266 SFLR Page 2
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 lice nse plates. The notice shall contain all necessary information
2 and shall contain instructions for the renewal procedure upon
3 presentation to a licensed operator or Service Oklahoma. The
4 license plates shall be issued on a staggered system.
5 On and after January 1, 2022, if a special license plate is
6 issued pursuant to this section, any registration fee required for
7 such plate pursuant to this section and the fee required pursuant to
8 Section 1132 of this title shall be remitted at the same time and
9 subject to a single registration period. Service Oklahoma shall
10 determine, by rule, a method for making required fee and
11 registration period adjustments if a special license plate is
12 obtained during a twelve-month period for which a registration fee
13 has already been remitted pursuant to Section 1132 of this title.
14 The combination of fees in a single remittance shall not alter the
15 apportionment otherwise provided for in this section.
16 Service Oklahoma is hereby directed to develop and implement a
17 system whereby licensed operators are permitted to accept
18 applications for special license plates authorized under this
19 section. The licensed operator shall confirm the applicant's
20 eligibility, if applicable, collect and deposit any amount
21 specifically authorized by law, accept and process the necessary
22 information directly into such system and generate a receipt
23 accordingly. For performance of these duties, licensed operators
24 shall retain the fee provided in Section 1141.1 of this title for
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - HB4266 SFLR Page 3
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 regi stration of a motor vehicle. The licensed operator fees for
2 acceptance of applications and renewals shall be paid out of the
3 Oklahoma Tax Commission Reimbursement Fund. Beginning January 1,
4 2023, the licensed operator fees for acceptance of applications and
5 renewals shall be paid out of the Service Oklahoma Reimbursement
6 Fund.
7 If fewer than one hundred of any type of special license plates
8 authorized prior to January 1, 2004, are issued prior to January 1,
9 2006, Service Oklahoma shall discontinue issuance and renewal of
10 that type of special license plate. Any such authorized special
11 license plate registrant shall be allowed to display the license
12 plate upon the designated vehicle until the registration expiration
13 date. After such time the expired special license plate shall be
14 removed from the vehicle.
15 Except as otherwise provided in law, for special license plates
16 authorized on or after July 1, 2004, no special license plates shall
17 be developed or issued by Service Oklahoma until Service Oklahoma
18 receives one hundred (100) prepaid applications therefor. The
19 prepaid applications must be received by Service Oklahoma within one
20 hundred eighty (180) days of the effective date of the authorization
21 or the authority to issue shall be null and void. In the event one
22 hundred (100) prepaid applications are not received by Service
23 Oklahoma within such prescribed time period any payment so received
24 shall be refunded accordingly.
